snippet.title: What is Auditing? | Who is an Auditor? | Objectives of Auditing
snippet.description:
In this video, we have explained the meaning of auditing and its need in layman language. Further, you will find the features of auditing. Next, you will get to know the meaning of an auditor. At the end of this video we have explained the objectives of auditing.

Basically, audit is the financial investigation conducted by an auditor - internal or external, to find out whether they are accurate and free from any material misstatements. After the completion of the audit, auditor gives an opinion on the truthfulness and fairness of the financial statements.

snippet.title: Calculating the Mean, Variance and Standard Deviation, Clearly Explained!!!
snippet.description:
One of the most basic things we do all the time in Data Analysis (i.e. Statistics, Machine Learning or any other sort of number crunching type thing) is calculate the mean, variance and standard deviation. This StatQuest walks you through these tasks and help you avoid a very common pitfall that is all too easy to fall into.

NOTE: This StatQuest assumes are already familiar with...

...Histograms: https://youtu.be/qBigTkBLU6g
...Statistical Distributions: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oI3hZJqXJuc
...the Normal Distribution: https://youtu.be/rzFX5NWojp0
...and Population Parameters: https://youtu.be/vikkiwjQqfU

NOTE: For more details on why dividing by 'n' underestimates the population variance and why we square each term, check out the follow up StatQuest: https://youtu.be/sHRBg6BhKjI

snippet.title: Neural Networks Pt. 1: Inside the Black Box
snippet.description:
Neural Networks are one of the most popular Machine Learning algorithms, but they are also one of the most poorly understood. Everyone says Neural Networks are "black boxes", but that's not true at all. In this video I break each piece down and show how it works, step-by-step, using simple mathematics that is still true to the algorithm. By the end of this video you will have a deep understanding of what Neural Networks do.

For a complete index of all the StatQuest videos, check out:
https://statquest.org/video-index/

snippet.title: The Chain Rule
snippet.description:
The Chain Rule is a method for finding complex derivatives and is used all the time in Statistics and Machine Learning. This video breaks it down into its two simple pieces and shows you how they easily come together. We then use the Chain Rule to solve a common Machine Learning problem - optimizing the Residual Squared Loss Function.

snippet.title: Gradient Descent, Step-by-Step
snippet.description:
Gradient Descent is the workhorse behind most of Machine Learning. When you fit a machine learning method to a training dataset, you're probably using Gradient Descent. It can optimize parameters in a wide variety of settings. Since it's so fundamental to Machine Learning, I decided to make a "step-by-step" video that shows you exactly how it works.

NOTE: This video assumes you are already familiar with Least Squares and Linear Regression. If not, here's the link to the Quest: https://youtu.be/PaFPbb66DxQ

For a complete index of all the StatQuest videos, check out:
https://statquest.org/video-index/

Sources:
There are a ton of websites that describe the math behind Gradient Descent. One of my favorite is the wikipedia article: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient_descent

snippet.title: Introduction to MATLAB in 8 Minutes | What is MATLAB? | MATLAB for Beginners | Simplilearn
snippet.description:
This video on "Introduction to MATLAB in 8 minutes" will cover the basic concepts of MATLAB like its definition, features, Advantages, and disadvantages of MATLAB and usage with the career opportunities in it. By the end of this video, you will understand MATLAB, a high-level programing language, and the importance of learning it. 

This video will cover the following.
00:00 Introduction
01:25 What is MATLAB?
01:50 Features of MATLAB
03:03 Advantages and disadvantages of MATLAB
04:35 Usage of MATLAB
06:06 Career opportunities of MATLAB

 What is MATLAB? 
MATLAB is a software used for high-performance visualization, mathematical computation, and programming. MATLAB stands for "Matrix Laboratory," as it was   originally known as the matrix programming language.

Features of MATLAB  
1.High-Level Language 
2.Interactive environment 
3.Handling graphics 
4.Mathematical function library 
5.Toolbox 

Advantages and Disadvantages of MATLAB
Advantages 
1.Ease of use 
2.Platform independence
3.Predefined Functions 
4.Device-Independent Plotting  
5.Graphical User Interface. 

Disadvantages 
1.Interpreted language 
2.The Cost

Career opportunities in MATLAB
1.Data Scientist - Data science is a field that grows at lightning speed, and often uses MATLAB in their work. The average salary for this position is  10.0 Lakhs in India and $145358 in the US.

2.Machine Learning Expert - Another new field heavily relies on MATLAB is AI and machine learning. The average salary of a machine learning expert is  8,50006 in India and $1,36,396 in the US.

3.Control Systems Engineer - Control systems engineers design and implement various dynamic systems. The average salary for this position is 6.2 Lakhs in India and  $97,955 per year in the US.

4.Computational Finance Specialist - Computational finance uses computer-based tools and techniques to solve practical problems related to finance. The average salary for this position is 7,06771 per year in India and $82,488 in the US.

What is Matlab?
MATLAB is a versatile computer program that performs mathematical calculations, visualization, and programming at high speed.
The GUI of Matlab is very user-friendly and interactive.
Generally, a variable is used to store data. And can store any kind of data like a scalar, vector, and matrices. 
Basically, there are three methods to initialize a variable in MATLAB:
It assigns data to the variable in an assignment statement.
It input data into the variable from the keyboard.
It reads data from a file.
An operator is a symbol that tells the compiler to perform various numerical or logical operations. 
There are several types of operators in Matlab, like 
Arithmetic operator 
Arithmetic Array operator
Relational operators
Relational Array operators
Logical and Bitwise Operators 

Functions are tasks or a set of tasks that are performed on a given set of input that converts the input into a preferred output. 
Some of the common functions in Matlab are,
Trigonometric function
Exponential function 
logarithmic functions
and Square roots

snippet.description:

This Matlab Programming video will go over the fundamental statements and functions that must be understood when writing a program in Matlab. In this video, we've also gone over some of the basic programs. I am sure that by the end of this video, you will be able to write programs in Matlab

In this video, we will cover
00:00 Matlab Programming
01:24 Environmental Programming 
02:06 Control statements
09:55 Matlab Loops
21:29 Try-catch Statements 
23:01 Arrays in Matlab 
28:11 Basic Programs in Matlab 

The shortcuts of Matlab 
Clc - used to clear the command window 
Clear - used to remove the workspace 
Diary - here a copy of all inputs and most of the outputs typed in the command window will be echoed in the diary file.
Along with these, we have diary off-  It suspends input into the diary file. And diary on - It resumes input again.
Which -   It tells which version of a file is being executed and where it is located.

A loop statement allows us to execute a statement or group of statements multiple times. 
Generally, there are two types of looping, 
First, For loop - A for loop is used to repeat a statement or a group of statements a fixed number of times.
And the second one is a while loop. A while loop is used to execute a statement or a group of statements an infinite number of times until the conditional specified by while is false. 

The break statement terminates the execution of a for loop or while loop.

The continue statement works within a for or while loop and passes control to the next iteration.

snippet.title: How to Create Mockups In Figma? | Figma UI UX Design Tutorial | UI UX For Beginners | Simplilearn
snippet.description:
https://www.simplilearn.com/caltech-ui-ux-bootcamp?utm_campaign=HowToCreateMockupsUsingFigma&utm_medium=Descriptionff&utm_source=youtube  

This video on How to create mockups in Figma is a demo-based tutorial that will help you understand how to make mockups in Figma and give some helpful hints for making the most of this powerful tool. In this Figma Ui UX Design tutorial, you will understand the use of mockups, which enable designers to check out their concepts and receive feedback early in the development process, is essential in the design process and how Figma is an excellent tool for generating mockups since it gives you a lot of customizing choices and capabilities. Below are the topics discussed in this Ui Ux for beginners tutorial. 

00:00 Introducction
01:03 What are mockups?
01:36 How to create mockups in Figma?
02:13 Desigining apps and websites in Figma

 What are Mockups?

Mockups are merely designs that represent how a service or product will seem in the future. Anything from websites and mobile applications to basic things like packaging may use them.
Before devoting excessive time and money to a particular design, mockups allow designers to test their ideas quickly. Additionally, they allow designers to gather early client or other stakeholder comments, which can assist in enhancing the finished product.

 How to create Mockups in figma?

Figma is an excellent tool for generating mockups since it gives you a lot of customization choices and capabilities. Create a new file in Figma and choose the "Mockup" template from the list of available templates to start creating mockups.

You can create mockups in Figma by accessing hundreds of premium Artboard Studio mockup components within your Figma files. With only a button press, quickly convert Figma frames into realistic product mockups.

snippet.description:
This video on Top 10 Programming languages in 2023 will take you through the most trending and in-demand programming languages in the market. As 2023 is approaching soon, tech geeks are already curious to know which programming language is best to learn and will be in demand for 2023. These Top 10 Programming languages are important for your career growth in the year 2023. The Top 10 Programming languages for 2023 mentioned in the video are expected to create vast demand and open many career opportunities. So, what are you waiting for? 

10. Rust: Rust is a multi-paradigm, general-purpose programming language developed by Firefox as an operational replacement for C++.

9. Golang: Google Designed a simple and statistically typed programming language Golang that is a brilliant combination of advanced memory safety and Garbage collection with the simplicity of the C language.

8. Kotlin: Kotlin is the future programming language that surpasses Java. Peculiarly, theres more Java can do than just develop android. Kotiln just makes things easier for android when compared to Java. 

7. SQL: SQL is a data language used to create data tables. It stores data, communicates with the database, and manipulates data to fetch the required results, a major part of data analytics.

6. TypeScript shares similarities with JavaScript but follows strict syntactical practices with brilliant tooling at any scale.

5. Swift: Swift was one of the oldest programming languages that needed programmers to be well aware of a large variety of libraries. Objective C was verbose and time-consuming to adapt.

4. C/C++: C is titled the mother of all programming languages. The veteran programming language has contributed a lot to developing new languages, compilers, databases, and one of the most popular operating systems, Microsoft Windows.

3. JavaScript: JavaScript. The most versatile and powerful programming language that turned the face of the internet. Javascript is a leading programming language with the highest number of communities and active users worldwide. 

2. Java: Java has the largest community, repositories, and support among all Programming languages. It has spread its roots into every software framework, mobile application, Big Data, and operating system; you name it, Java did it.

1. Python: Many believe that python is one of the newest programming languages. As a matter of fact, its a veteran programming language that is a lot older than Java.

That concludes our list of top programming languages for the year 2023.

snippet.title: Top 10 Dying Programming Languages in 2023 | Programming Languages to Avoid in 2023 | Simplilearn
snippet.description:
Post Graduate Program In Full Stack Web Development: https://www.simplilearn.com/pgp-full-stack-web-development-certification-training-course?utm_campaign=Top10DyingProgrammingLanguagesin2023-51mUwZ6J2D4&utm_medium=Descriptionff&utm_source=youtube
Caltech Coding Bootcamp (US Only): https://www.simplilearn.com/coding-bootcamp?utm_campaign=Top10DyingProgrammingLanguagesin2023-51mUwZ6J2D4&utm_medium=Descriptionff&utm_source=youtube

This video is based on the *Top 10 dying programming languages in 2023* , which will inform you about the top 10 programming languages that will be outdated in 2023. If you are planning to upskill yourself and improve your programming skills, then this video will help you understand the programming languages to avoid in 2023. 

Here is the list of *Top 10 Dying Programming Languages 2023*
 00:00 *Top 10 Dying Programming Languages 2023*
 01:02 *CoffeeScript*
*CoffeeScript* is one of the lightest languages ever designed. CoffeeScript was adopted by major companies like dropbox, GitHub, etc to develop their browser-side code. JavaScript is a better alternative; in past years CoffeeScript was declared obsolete.

 01:36 *Ruby*
*Ruby* is extensively used in building web applications, data processing, automation and many more. Python being strong competitor in terms of readablility and code security than Ruby, Ruby slowly became obsolete and is in the list of dying programming languages

 02:16 *VBA*
*VBA* was one of the most extensively used programming languages. Despite being based on .NET, it is no longer updated by Microsoft, indicating its obsolescence.

 02:55 *Scala*
*Scala* performance was not the issue however, most developers were unaware of features of Scala. Thereby, adding it in the list of dying programming languages

 03:27 *Objective C*
Verbose nature, complex syntax, and outdated libraries of *Objective C*, made developers switch to swift for the ease of code readability and application development, thus adding it to the list of dying programming languages

 04:06 *Perl* 
It is one of the most efficient open-source languages for text manipulation. Despite its simplicity and efficiency, *Perl* comes with a major drawback. Perl fails to support portability because of CPAN modules. Programs run slowly and must be interpreted each time any changes are made. 

 04:45 *Haskell*
*Haskell* has faced issues like no proper IDE support, complex syntax, and a steep learning curve. This forced developers to migrate to better alternatives, thereby adding it into the list of dying programming languages.

*Top 3 Dying Programming Languages 2023*

 05:26 *Fortran*
*Fortran* is in the list of dying programming languages because developers soon had to migrate to other languages due to a lack of dynamic memory, reliability, and unsafe code prone to cyber threats. 

 06:05 *Erlang*
*Erlang* supported banking, e-commerce, computer systems development, and instant messaging services. Due to its complex debugging procedures and critical deployment issues it is not in use recent days.

 06:41 *Cobol*
The early main frame programming for business transactions, banking, and many more was handled by *COBOL*. It had a tougher verbose syntax with slow compilation and deployment.

snippet.title: Top 10 Technologies To Learn In 2023 | Trending Technologies In 2023 | Simplilearn
snippet.description:
This video on *Top 10 Technologies to Learn in 2023* brings to you the trending technologies in 2023 that you should watch out for. With time, new technologies are evolving, technologies that help address global challenges and those that will make life simpler in the coming years.

00:00 *Top 10 Technologies To Learn In 2023*

 01:02 *Extended Reality*
The extended reality, or XR, covers everything that falls under Augmented Reality, Virtual Reality, Mixed Reality, or anything in between AR and VR. Extended Reality is estimated to reach USD 397. 81 billion by the end of 2026, with a CAGR of 57. 91%.

 02:11 *Edge Computing*
Edge computing is a distributed computing pattern that brings data storage and computation closer to the data source, thereby improving the response time and saving the bandwidth. It is estimated to reach USD 9200 by the end of 2023 with a CAGR of 27.3%. And so it takes 9th place in the list of top 10 technologies to learn in 2023. 

 02:52 *5G / Wifi 6*
5G networks are estimated to have more than 1.7 billion subscribers across the globe. By 2026,5G Services Market is anticipated to increase from 53.0 billion USD to 249.2 billion USD.  

 03:58 *Blockchain*
Blockchain is one of the contemporary technologies with a bright future. Blockchain is expected to reach USD 19.9 billion with a CAGR of 42.8%. Thus this really makes a point of adding blockchain to the list of top 10 technologies to learn in 2023.

 04:43 *Cybersecurity (Digital Trust)*
As per recent reports, the global cybersecurity market size is expected to reach 31.82 billion USD by the end of 2023, with a CAGR of 15.2%. Thereby taking 6th position on the list of top 10 technologies.

 05:33 *Robotics And Automation*
Robotics is a significant industry that is gaining momentum with time. The robotics market is estimated to reach $70.84 million by the end of 2023, with a CAGR of 10.5%. 

 06:35 *IoT*
IoT devices are increasing by almost 31 percent every year, and according to reports, there will be 30 billion IoT devices by 2022. It is estimated that the market value will reach or even exceed $1.6 trillion by the end of 2023 and so it on the 4th position in the list of top 10 technologies 2023

 07:23 *Quantum Computing*
Quantum Computing uses the properties of quantum physics to perform calculations and simulations that would not be possible on a traditional machine. Quantum computing market is estimated to reach US$411.4 Million by 2026 with a CAGR of 24.2%.

 08:25 *Web 3.0*
Decentralized cryptocurrency networks must ensure that transactions are carried out safely and securely without the involvement of a centralized organization like Visa or PayPal. It is estimated that the market value will reach till $69 billion by the end of 2030. 

 09:45 *AI and AIaaS*
AI or Artificial Intelligence is the top most trending technology these days. It enables machines to think and act like humans. It is projected to reach USD 42.4 billion with a CAGR of 29.75%.

snippet.title: How to Apply for German Universities? | Steps to Study in Germany For 2022 | Simplilearn
snippet.description:
In this video on How to apply to German universities, you will learn in brief about all the steps to study in Germany. We will understand about the aptitude test, required documents, university requirements, and much more. We will also cover topics like applying for a student visa for Germany, learning the German language, and enrolling at university. 

How to Apply for German Universities - 
0:00 Introduction
1:07 Basic research on universities
2:12 Study requirements
2:27 University entrance qualifications
3:11 Aptitude test
3:54 Required documents
4:14 University requirements
5:23 Learn the German language
5:50 Apply for student visa
6:45 Enrolling at university

The most desirable country for international students that do not speak English is Germany. It is recognized for its top universities that provide students with affordable, high-quality education. Germany is home to dozens of world-class universities, as well as lively cities brimming with art galleries and exciting nightlife. German universities provide internationally renowned courses in law, computer science, medicine, engineering, and social science.

 Basic research on universities
You can begin the University research in advance by making a list of topics you are passionate about and look into occupations or study areas that are linked to those topics. You can also get in touch with former students from the German universities you're interested in which may give you a better understanding of the curriculum.

 University requirements
 DSH examination: The test is designed to evaluate your reading, writing, listening, and speaking skills. The test is totally focused according to the classroom format, and as a result, the circumstances you might encounter while taking the course will be the basis for the questions.
 TestDaF: TestDaF is a language exam for international German learners who want to study in Germany. The subjects are based on critical communication challenges in lectures, discussions, or working groups, as well as other university-related activities.
 Goethe-Zertifikat C2: This exam includes modules for reading, listening, writing, and speaking. The four modules can be taken separately or together, with four different module certificates equal to a single all-round certificate.

 Apply for student Visa: Types of Visas
 Prospective student visa: This visa is intended for students who have not yet received their university admissions decisions and are awaiting the outcomes of their final application processes. 
 Student Visa: The student visa is intended for students who have already been accepted to a school in Germany. This visa is only valid for three months. During these three months, you must apply for your residence permit at your city's Foreigners' Registration Office.

 Enrolling at University
The enrollment confirmation document is known as a "Immatrikulationsbescheinigung." You'll need it in the future as it's a crucial document. The enrolling period is frequently very brief. A student ID will be sent to you once you have registered. Once you have received formal enrollment status, you are able to attend university classes

snippet.title: Take Courses From Top Universities in Coursera For Free
snippet.description:
In this video, I shared how to audit the courses in Coursera for free. If you do not know about Coursera, it's a massive online course platform. You can take almost all the courses for free through the audit option. In the audit option, you can access all the course materials. Probably not a few assignments. If you cannot finish the course on time, you can audit the same course again. You can audit one course as many times as you want.

#datascience #dataanalytics #coursera #learning

snippet.title: 1.2 Install packages by conda install or pip install
snippet.description:
In order to install python packages, you can (on a Windows machine) go to: 
Start - Anaconda3 - Anaconda Prompt
In the Anaconda Prompt, you can write:
"conda install" and then the package name.
If this does not work, then you can write:
"pip install" and then the package name.

snippet.title: Enzymes: Features, Functions and Classification and enzyme activity: "Short Notes! - 2mins"
snippet.description:
This video explains about Enzymes, properties of enzymes, Functions of enzymes and the Classification of enzymes and the factors affecting enzyme activity in under 2 minutes.

Enzymes are biological catalysts that speeds up the biochemical reactions. Enzymes acts on substrate to generate products. During this process enzyme will be not consumed.

Enzymes are highly specific and interacts with one or few substrates only.

Most of the enzymes are made up of proteins. Ribozyme is exception to this and it is made of RNA.

Enzyme reduces the activation energy required for a reaction there by increasing the speed of reaction.

Enzyme activity or velocity is the rate of enzyme catalysed reaction, generally it is expressed as mmoles of product formed per min/mg of enzyme.

snippet.title: CRISPR Cas for disease diagnosis: "Short Note! - 2 min"
snippet.description:
This video explains about CRISPR Cas system for infectious disease diagnosis.

CRISPR Cas system tool box now has many enzymes that can specifically match and cleave DNA / RNA with the help of guideRNA.

Collateral Cleavage, the key feature of Cas12/13 is now used for cleaving reporter probe to identify the presence of specific pathogen.

Recently FDA approved Covid-19 / SARS CoV 2 diagnosis using CRISPR - Cas technology. These includes SHERLOCK COVID-19 and FELUDA, which used CRISPR-Cas9.

snippet.title: FRET: Fluorescence Resonance Energy Transfer - "Short Note! - 2mins"
snippet.description:
FRET: Fluorescence Resonance Energy Transfer or Forster resonance energy transfer 

FRET relies on the distance-dependent transfer of energy from a donor molecule to an acceptor molecule. Due to its sensitivity to distance, FRET has been used to investigate molecular interactions.

Cyan Fluorescent Protein and Yellow Fluorescent Protein pairs are the most commonly used FRET pairs for protein protein interaction studies.

snippet.title: Apoenzyme, Cofactors, Coenzymes and Holoenzymes -"Short Note! - 2mins"
snippet.description:
This video explains about Apoenzyme, Cofactors, Coenzymes and Holoenzymes with examples.

Enzymes are biological catalysts, they speed up the biochemical reaction by reducing the activation energy.

The catalytic activity of many enzymes depends on the presence of small molecules called cofactors.
An enzyme without its cofactor is referred to as an apoenzyme; the complete, catalytically active enzyme is called a holoenzyme.
 
Cofactors can be subdivided into two groups:  
1. Metal Ions and 
2. Small organic molecules

The enzyme Taq DNA polymerase require Mg2+ for its activity, Lactate dehydrogenase requires small organic molecule Nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide.

snippet.title: Diauxic Growth Curve
snippet.description:
This video explains about diauxic growth curve. When bacteria cells are grown on a media containing glucose and lactose carbon sources, bacterial cells utilize glucose initially and grows exponentially. once the glucose is depleted, it prepares the system for utilization of lactose by producing enzymes required for metabolizing lactose. This is done by lac operon regulation. For this bacterial cells enters a second lag phase or the preparatory phase.

This type of growth curve is called as Diauxic growth curve or biphasic growth curve.

snippet.title: Arabinose Operon / ara Operon
snippet.description:
www.technologyinsciene.blogspot.com

Arabinose operon also known as ara Operon, is an operon required for the metabolism of arabinose.

Operon are groups of genes clustered in the bacterial DNA regulating the expression of functionally related proteins.

In E. coli half of the genes are clustered into operons which are involved in particular metabolic pathways.

ara is an example of complex gene regulation. ara Operon is responsible for the metabolism of arabinose.

snippet.title: Tryptophan (trp) Operon
snippet.description:
www.technologyinscience.blogspot.com

Genes for amino acid synthesis is clustered in operons. Trp operon regulates the biosynthesis of tryptophan. Tryptophan is an amino acid, whose levels are controlled by trp operon.
Trp operon has operator, trp regulator, trp Leader sequence and five structural genes for the expression of enzymes required for the tryptophan synthesis
Tryptophan levels are regulated by 2 mechanisms:
1. Repressor mediated
2. Transcription attenuation mediated

Tryptophan biosynthesis regulation is based on repressor mediated and the fine tuning on the rate of synthesis is by transcription attenuation.
